1:# Rhei Agents Specification
3:This document specifies how Rhei integrates with coding agents — the CLI tools that execute work on tasks. It covers agent configuration, resolution order, invocation profiles, prompt composition, parallel execution, timeout handling, and log capture.
7:## Overview
9:Rhei can spawn coding agents directly from `rhei run`. Instead of requiring hand-written `workflow.sh` callback scripts, the run command resolves an agent for each task, composes a prompt from the state machine instructions, and spawns the agent as a subprocess. The spawned agent does the work for the current state, writes any required artifacts, and exits. `rhei run` remains the transition authority: after the subprocess exits, the engine evaluates the declared forward transitions and performs the state change itself. Callbacks still fire on transitions — agents and callbacks are complementary.
