618:## `rhei run` — Agent Mode
620:### CLI
623:rhei run <RHEI_PLAN> [--dry-run] [--no-callbacks] [--no-agent] [--no-program]
624:                     [--agent <AGENT>] [--model <MODEL>] [--continue-on-error]
625:                     [--parallel <N>] [--program-timeout <DURATION>]
630:| `--dry-run` | false | Show what would be spawned without executing |
632:| `--no-agent` | false | Disable agent spawning; fall back to callback-only advancement (pre-agent behavior) |
633:| `--no-program` | false | Disable program spawning; fall back to callback-only advancement for program states |
634:| `--agent <AGENT>` | | Override the agent transport for this run |
635:| `--model <MODEL>` | | Override the model profile id for this run |
636:| `--continue-on-error` | false | Continue to the next task when an agent or program exits non-zero |
637:| `--parallel <N>` | 1 | Maximum number of agents/programs to run concurrently. `0` means unlimited. |
638:| `--program-timeout <DURATION>` | | Override program timeout for this run (e.g., `10m`, `1h`). See [Program States Specification](rhei-programs.spec.md#timeout-handling). |
